        "text_bphdMj": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>I vividly remember my 8th birthday and how I celebrated as I always had - digging into phirni, served in an earthen pot, and laced with the delicate gold of saffron.</p><p>This was in my Kashmiri neighbor's house in Calcutta (now Kolkata) where I was born to parents from states at other ends of the country (Punjab and Rajasthan). I recall the occasion now as it was a precursor of my kaleidoscopic journey across the subcontinent.</p>",
            "text_size": "typeset",
            "secondary_color": true
          }
        }
